### PrepPanda API — HTTP Test Suite
### Compatible with: VS Code REST Client · JetBrains HTTP Client · httpYac
###
### Usage
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 1. Start the server:
###      uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
###
### 2. Fill in the @chapter_id variable after running §2 (ingest chapter).
###    You can copy the UUID from the response body.
###
### Variables — edit as needed
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@base       = http://localhost:8000
@admin_key  = preppanda-admin-secret
@book_id    = FILL_AFTER_§1       # paste UUID from §1 response
@chapter_id = FILL_AFTER_§2       # paste UUID from §2 response


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 0 ── HEALTH CHECK
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 0.1  Server liveness
# @name health
GET {{base}}/health
Accept: application/json


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1 ── ADMIN: BOOKS
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1.1  Create a book  →  copy book_id into @book_id above
# @name create_book
POST {{base}}/admin/books
X-Admin-Key: {{admin_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title":   "Biology Part I – Class XI",
  "grade":   11,
  "subject": "biology"
}


### 1.2  Create a book — wrong admin key (expect 403)
POST {{base}}/admin/books
X-Admin-Key: wrong-key
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title":   "Should Fail",
  "grade":   10,
  "subject": "chemistry"
}


### 1.3  Create a book — no admin key (expect 403)
POST {{base}}/admin/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title":   "Also Fails",
  "grade":   9,
  "subject": "physics"
}


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2 ── ADMIN: CHAPTERS  (multipart form + PDF upload)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2.1  Ingest a chapter PDF  →  copy chapter_id into @chapter_id above
###      Replace the file path with the actual path to your PDF.
# @name ingest_chapter
POST {{base}}/admin/books/{{book_id}}/chapters
X-Admin-Key: {{admin_key}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----PrepPandaBoundary

------PrepPandaBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="chapter_number"

1
------PrepPandaBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="chapter_title"

Sexual Reproduction in Flowering Plants
------PrepPandaBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdf"; filename="lebo101.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./lebo101.pdf
------PrepPandaBoundary--


### 2.2  Ingest chapter — book not found (expect 404)
POST {{base}}/admin/books/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/chapters
X-Admin-Key: {{admin_key}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----PrepPandaBoundary

------PrepPandaBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="chapter_number"

1
------PrepPandaBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="chapter_title"

Nonexistent Chapter
------PrepPandaBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdf"; filename="dummy.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./lebo101.pdf
------PrepPandaBoundary--


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 3 ── ADMIN: PYQs (raw text block format in form body)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 3.1  Ingest PYQs via form text body — single Q+A pair
# @name ingest_pyqs_form
POST {{base}}/admin/books/{{book_id}}/chapters/{{chapter_id}}/pyqs
X-Admin-Key: {{admin_key}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

body=---Q+5M+2022%0AWhat+is+double+fertilisation%3F+Where+and+how+does+it+take+place%3F%0A---%0A%0A---Ans%0ADouble+fertilisation+is+a+phenomenon+characteristic+of+angiosperms.+In+this+process%2C+out+of+the+two+male+gametes%2C+one+fuses+with+the+egg+cell+%28syngamy%29+and+the+other+fuses+with+the+two+polar+nuclei+%28triple+fusion%29.%0A---


### 3.2  Ingest PYQs — multiple blocks with and without answers
# @name ingest_pyqs_multi
POST {{base}}/admin/books/{{book_id}}/chapters/{{chapter_id}}/pyqs
X-Admin-Key: {{admin_key}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----PrepPandaBoundary

------PrepPandaBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="body"

---Q 3M 2021
Name the parts of an angiosperm flower in which development of
male and female gametophyte takes place.
---

---Ans
Male gametophyte develops in the microsporangia (anther).
Female gametophyte develops in the megasporangia (ovule).
---

---Q 2M 2019
What is emasculation? When and why does a plant breeder employ it?
---

---Ans
Emasculation is the removal of anthers from a bisexual flower before
pollen is shed. It is done to prevent self-pollination in artificial
hybridisation experiments.
---

---Q 5M NEET 2023
Explain the structure of a mature embryo sac. How does double
fertilisation occur and what is its significance?
---

---Q 1M 2020
Define apomixis.
---

---Ans
Apomixis is a mode of asexual reproduction that mimics sexual
reproduction; seeds are produced without fertilisation.
---
------PrepPandaBoundary--


### 3.3  Ingest PYQs — malformed (no valid blocks, expect 422)
POST {{base}}/admin/books/{{book_id}}/chapters/{{chapter_id}}/pyqs
X-Admin-Key: {{admin_key}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----PrepPandaBoundary

------PrepPandaBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="body"

This is just plain text with no block markers at all.
------PrepPandaBoundary--


### 3.4  Ingest PYQs — chapter not found (expect 404)
POST {{base}}/admin/books/{{book_id}}/chapters/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/pyqs
X-Admin-Key: {{admin_key}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----PrepPandaBoundary

------PrepPandaBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="body"

---Q 2M 2022
What is pollination?
---
------PrepPandaBoundary--


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 4 ── ADMIN: PYQs (file upload)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 4.1  Ingest PYQs via .txt file upload
###      The file should contain PYQ blocks in the block format.
# @name ingest_pyqs_file
POST {{base}}/admin/books/{{book_id}}/chapters/{{chapter_id}}/pyqs/file
X-Admin-Key: {{admin_key}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----PrepPandaBoundary

------PrepPandaBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="pyqs.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

---Q 4M CBSE 2022
Describe the post-fertilisation changes in a flower.
---

---Ans
After fertilisation: (1) The zygote develops into an embryo.
(2) The primary endosperm nucleus develops into endosperm.
(3) Ovules develop into seeds. (4) Ovary develops into fruit.
The other floral parts — petals, sepals, stamens, style, and stigma
— wither and fall off.
---

---Q 3M NEET 2021
What is triple fusion? Where does it occur?
---

---Ans
Triple fusion is the fusion of one male gamete with the two polar
nuclei to form the triploid (3n) primary endosperm nucleus (PEN).
It takes place in the central cell of the embryo sac.
---
------PrepPandaBoundary--


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 5 ── SRS: ASK
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 5.1  Ask a factual question
# @name srs_ask_factual
POST {{base}}/srs/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question":   "What is double fertilisation?",
  "chapter_id": "{{chapter_id}}"
}


### 5.2  Ask an analytical question
POST {{base}}/srs/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question":   "How do flowering plants ensure successful fertilisation despite having non-motile male gametes?",
  "chapter_id": "{{chapter_id}}"
}


### 5.3  Ask about a process (should trigger figure references)
POST {{base}}/srs/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question":   "Explain the structure of a mature embryo sac with reference to figures.",
  "chapter_id": "{{chapter_id}}"
}


### 5.4  Ask with chapter not found (expect 404)
POST {{base}}/srs/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question":   "What is photosynthesis?",
  "chapter_id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
}


### 5.5  Ask with too-short question (expect 422)
POST {{base}}/srs/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question":   "Hi",
  "chapter_id": "{{chapter_id}}"
}


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 6 ── MINDMAP: NESTED TREE
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 6.1  Get nested mind-map tree
# @name mindmap_tree
GET {{base}}/mindmap/{{chapter_id}}
Accept: application/json


### 6.2  Nested tree — chapter not found (expect 404)
GET {{base}}/mindmap/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Accept: application/json


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 7 ── MINDMAP: FLAT NODE LIST  (React-Flow / D3 force-graph format)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 7.1  Get flat node list with parent_ids
# @name mindmap_flat
GET {{base}}/mindmap/{{chapter_id}}/flat
Accept: application/json


### 7.2  Flat list — chapter not found (expect 404)
GET {{base}}/mindmap/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/flat
Accept: application/json


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 8 ── INGEST BOOK  — NCERT Biology Class 12 (one-shot, all 13 chapters)
#
# PDFs are in tests/Material/.  This sends all 13 lebo1xx.pdf files in
# a single multipart request.  The server creates the book record then
# runs NodeParser → VisualParser → Embedder → S3 for each chapter.
#
# This will take several minutes.  Watch server logs for per-chapter
# progress.  Copy the returned book_id into @bio12_book_id below, and
# any chapter_id you want to query into @bio12_chapter_id.
#
# ⚠  Raw PDFs (each up to ~65 MB) are uploaded to the bucket.
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@bio12_book_id    = FILL_AFTER_§8   # paste from §8.1 response → book_id
@bio12_chapter_id = FILL_AFTER_§8   # paste any chapter_id from §8.1 response

### 8.1  Ingest all 13 chapters of NCERT Biology Class 12
###      File paths are relative to this .http file (tests/).
###      VS Code REST Client resolves them relative to the workspace root;
###      adjust the prefix if needed (e.g. Server/tests/Material/...).
# @name ingest_bio12
POST {{base}}/admin/ingest-book
X-Admin-Key: {{admin_key}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Bio12Boundary

------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

Biology Part I & II – Class XII
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="grade"

12
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="subject"

biology
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="chapters"

[
  {"number": 1,  "title": "Reproduction in Organisms"},
  {"number": 2,  "title": "Sexual Reproduction in Flowering Plants"},
  {"number": 3,  "title": "Human Reproduction"},
  {"number": 4,  "title": "Reproductive Health"},
  {"number": 5,  "title": "Principles of Inheritance and Variation"},
  {"number": 6,  "title": "Molecular Basis of Inheritance"},
  {"number": 7,  "title": "Evolution"},
  {"number": 8,  "title": "Human Health and Disease"},
  {"number": 9,  "title": "Strategies for Enhancement in Food Production"},
  {"number": 10, "title": "Microbes in Human Welfare"},
  {"number": 11, "title": "Biotechnology: Principles and Processes"},
  {"number": 12, "title": "Biotechnology and Its Applications"},
  {"number": 13, "title": "Organisms and Populations"}
]
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdfs"; filename="lebo101.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Material/lebo101.pdf
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdfs"; filename="lebo102.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Material/lebo102.pdf
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdfs"; filename="lebo103.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Material/lebo103.pdf
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdfs"; filename="lebo104.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Material/lebo104.pdf
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdfs"; filename="lebo105.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Material/lebo105.pdf
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdfs"; filename="lebo106.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Material/lebo106.pdf
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdfs"; filename="lebo107.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Material/lebo107.pdf
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdfs"; filename="lebo108.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Material/lebo108.pdf
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdfs"; filename="lebo109.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Material/lebo109.pdf
------Bio12Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pdfs"; filename="lebo110.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./Material/lebo110.pdf
------Bio12Boundary
